verbs.description: unbarrel (third-person singular simple present unbarrels, present participle unbarreling or unbarrelling, simple past and past participle unbarreled or unbarrelled)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To unpack from a barrel or barrels.
examples: The remainder of the men were employed in unbarreling our Pork and stringing it on poles for convenience of carriage, and carrying our Batteaux from the river to the pond.
